window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>The true story of John Battaglia - the coldhearted father who executed his two young daughters to spite his ex-wife</i></p> <p>Dallas antiques dealer Mary Jean Pearle had a bitter history with her ex-husband, John David Battaglia, a former Marine and successful accountant - but even after the abuse she endured from him, she never thought he would go after their daughters, Faith and Liberty.</p> <p>That is, until she listened helplessly over the phone as Faith made a heartrending plea for her life - which was followed by gunshots.</p> <p>In this updated account of Battaglia's unthinkable crime - an act of filicide that was featured on <i>20/20</i> and would ultimately lead Texas to carry out the death sentence - Irene Pence recounts an unforgettable saga of violence, betrayal, and a mother's worst nightmare.</p> <p><i>Contains mature themes.</i></p>"; 
